[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " What then shall we say that Abraham, our ancestor according to the flesh,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has discovered regarding this matter?"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For if Abraham was declared righteous"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " by the works of the law, he has something to boast about – but not before God. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For what does the scripture say? “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "Abraham believed God"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "and it was credited"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": " to him as righteousness"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ".”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now to the one who works, his pay is not credited due to grace but due to obligation."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But to the one who does not work, but believes in the one who declares the ungodly righteous,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " his faith is credited as righteousness."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So even David himself speaks regarding the blessedness of the man to whom God credits righteousness apart from works:"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "Blessed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": " are those whose lawless deeds are forgiven, and whose sins are covered; "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "blessed is the one "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": " against whom the Lord will never count"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "sin"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Is this blessedness"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " then for"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the circumcision"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " or also for"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the uncircumcision? For we say, “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "faith "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "was credited to"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Abraham "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "as righteousness"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ".”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " How then was it credited to him? Was he circumcised at the time, or not? No, he was not circumcised but uncircumcised! "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And he received the sign of circumcision as a seal of the righteousness that he had by faith while he was still uncircumcised,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " so that he would become"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the father of all those who believe but have never been circumcised,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " that they too could have righteousness credited to them. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And he is also the father of the circumcised,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " who are not only circumcised, but who also walk in the footsteps of the faith that our father Abraham possessed when he was still uncircumcised."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For the promise"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to Abraham or to his descendants that he would inherit the world was not fulfilled through the law, but through the righteousness that comes by faith. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For if they become heirs by the law, faith is empty and the promise is nullified."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For the law brings wrath, because where there is no law there is no transgression"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " either. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For this reason it is by faith so that it may be by grace,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " with the result that the promise may be certain to all the descendants – not only to those who are under the law, but also to those who have the faith of Abraham,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " who is the father of us all "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (as it is written, “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "I have made you the father of many nations"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "”)."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He is our father"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in the presence of God whom he believed – the God who"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " makes the dead alive and summons the things that do not yet exist as though they already do."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Against hope Abraham"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " believed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in hope with the result that he became "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "the"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "father of many nations"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " according to the pronouncement,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "so will your descendants be"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ".”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Without being weak in faith, he considered"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " his own body as dead"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (because he was about one hundred years old) and the deadness of Sarah’s womb. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " did not waver in unbelief about the promise of God but was strengthened in faith, giving glory to God. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He was"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " fully convinced that what God"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " promised he was also able to do. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So indeed it was credited to Abraham"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " as righteousness."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But the statement"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": " it was credited to him"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " was not written only for Abraham’s"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " sake, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " but also for our sake, to whom it will be credited, those who believe in the one who raised Jesus our Lord from the dead. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " was given over"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " because of our transgressions and was raised for the sake of"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " our justification."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]